Definition: marked by artful prudence, expedience, and shrewdness
Example: it is neither polite nor politic to get into other people's quarrels; a politic decision; a politic manager; a politic old scoundrel; a shrewd and politic reply
Synonyms: IMPOLITIC, DIPLOMATIC, marked, by, artful, prudence, expedience, and, shrewdness, it, is, neither, polite, nor, politic, to, get, into, other, people, s, quarrels, a, decision, manager, old, scoundrel, shrewd, reply
Category: adj.all
